Given the solution variable u in the program, its gradient is obtained by grad(u) or nabla_grad(u).
However, the gradient of a piecewise continuous ﬁnite element scalar ﬁeld is a discontinuous vector ﬁeld since the φj has discontinuous derivatives at the boundaries of the cells. For example, using Lagrange elements of degree 1, u is linear over each cell, and the numerical ∇u becomes a piecewise

