The deepcopy=True argument signiﬁes a deep copy, which is a general term in computer science implying that a copy of the data is returned. (The opposite, deepcopy=False, means a shallow copy, where the returned objects are just pointers to the original data.)
The grad_u_x and grad_u_y variables behave as Function objects. In particular, we can extract the underlying arrays of nodal values by

