u = TrialFunction(V) v = TestFunction(V) u_k = interpolate(Constant(0.0), V) # previous (known) u a = inner(q(u_k)*nabla_grad(u), nabla_grad(v))*dx f = Constant(0.0)
L = f*v*dx

# Picard iterations

u = Function(V) eps = 1.0

# new unknown function # error measure ||u-u_k||

tol = 1.0E-5

# tolerance

iter = 0

# iteration counter

maxiter = 25

# max no of iterations allowed

while eps > tol and iter < maxiter:

iter += 1

solve(a == L, u, bcs) diff = u.vector().array() - u_k.vector().array()

eps = numpy.linalg.norm(diff, ord=numpy.Inf)

print "iter=%d: norm=%g" % (iter, eps) u_k.assign(u) # update for next iteration

We need to deﬁne the previous solution in the iterations, u_k, as a ﬁnite element function so that u_k can be updated with u at the end of the loop. We may create the initial Function u_k by interpolating
