The next task is to use a MeshFunction to mark all cells in Ω0 with the subdomain number 0 and all cells in Ω1 with the subdomain number 1. Our convention is to number subdomains as 0, 1, 2, . . ..
A MeshFunction is a discrete function that can be evaluated at a set of so-called mesh entities. Examples of mesh entities are cells, facets, and vertices. A MeshFunction over cells is suitable to represent subdomains (materials), while a MeshFunction over facets is used to represent pieces of external or internal boundaries. Mesh functions over vertices can be used to describe continuous ﬁelds.
2The term instance means a Python object of a particular type (such as SubDomain, Function, FunctionSpace, etc.). Many use instance and object as interchangeable terms. In other computer programming languages one may also use the term variable for the same thing. We mostly use the well-known term object in this text.

