2.4 Finite element function spaces
In the above discussion, we assumed that we could construct discrete subspaces Vh ⊂ V of inﬁnitedimensional function spaces. A central aspect of the ﬁnite element method is the construction of such subspaces by patching together local function spaces deﬁned by a set of ﬁnite elements. We here give a general overview of the construction of ﬁnite element function spaces and return in Chapters 3 and 4 to the construction of speciﬁc function spaces as subsets of H1, H(curl), H(div) and L2.

